<inglise> The Convention contains a number of clauses enabling transmitting and receiving agencies to resolve difficulties arising from a request for service, and these should be utilized before the central body is called upon. </inglise>
<eesti> Konventsioon sisaldab mitut s&auml;tet, mis v&otilde;imaldavad edastavatel ja vastuv&otilde;tvatel asutustel lahendada k&auml;tteandmistaotlusest tulenevaid probleeme ning enne keskasutuse poole p&ouml;&ouml;rdumist tuleks neid kasutada. </eesti>
<inglise> Thus a document ought not to be transmitted to the central body merely because it is not possible to determine the receiving agency with the relevant territorial jurisdiction; rather a request for information should be sent under Article 3 (a). </inglise>
